OL,3,CTata Steel: Unions vow to 'fight for
OL,4,CPort Talbot' as they take their
OL,5,Cprotests to Westminster
OL,7,FThe Indian conglomerate announced
OL,8,F2,800 positions will be lost at Port
OL,9,FTalbot as it transitions to a new,
OL,10,Fgreener form of steel production,
OL,11,Faided by #500m from the UK Government.
OL,13,FTata says a 45-day consultation will
OL,14,Fget underway as part of its plan to
OL,15,F"transform and restructure its UK
OL,16,Fbusiness".
OL,18,FHowever, unions have vowed to battle
OL,19,FTata's plans to ensure that
OL,20,Fsteelworkers' jobs will be protected.
