OL,3,CTata Steel: Unions vow to 'fight for
OL,4,CPort Talbot' as they take their
OL,5,Cprotests to Westminster
OL,7,F"We have to fight for Port Talbot, and
OL,8,FUnite will fight for that", he said.
OL,10,FThe Welsh Secretary, David TC Davies,
OL,11,Ftold Sharp End there is no other plan
OL,12,Fto save jobs in Port Talbot.
OL,14,FThe Secretary for State said it is
OL,15,F"fantasy politics" to think there is
OL,16,Fanother option to save jobs at the
OL,17,FTata Plant.
OL,19,FHe added, "I am very anxious there
OL,20,Fisn't anything to discourage Tata from
OL,21,F(...) putting in #750 million."
